Quote: RED COD (<i> Lotella Bacchus</i>). ... Red-cod (also called the yellow-tail and the haddock) is a well-known fish on some parts of the coast, being the species that is cured and sold as the Findon haddock. It is a handsome fish, with a brilliant play of metallic colours when alive.
